headline.main: Chess: Tal Wins the Chigorin Title At Sochi on the Black Sea

results.snippet: Mikhail Tal won the 16th Chigorin Memorial Tournament, held in the Black Sea resort of Sochi in the Soviet Union. The Latvian former world champion scored 10-5 against a strong field.   The surprising second-place finisher was 22-year-old Predrag...
results.lead_paragraph: Mikhail Tal won the 16th Chigorin Memorial Tournament, held in the Black Sea resort of Sochi in the Soviet Union. The Latvian former world champion scored 10-5 against a strong field. The surprising second-place finisher was 22-year-old Predrag Nikolic of Yugoslavia, whose 9 1/2-5 1/2 tally gave him his second and final grandmaster norm.
